cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "r.richdem: GRASS GIS add-on collection wrapping the RichDEM terrain-analysis library"
abstract: >
  A collection of seven GRASS GIS modules that expose the RichDEM Python
  bindings for depression filling, depression breaching, flat resolution,
  flow accumulation, terrain attributes, depression-hierarchy construction,
  and Fill-Spill-Merge surface-water routing.
authors:
  - family-names: "Wickert"
    given-names: "Andrew D."
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9545-3365"
contributors:
  - name: "Claude Sonnet 4.6 (Anthropic)"
    alias: "claude-sonnet-4-6"
    role: "software"
    notes: >
      AI assistant used to develop the GRASS GIS bindings, module code,
      shared library, and HTML documentation. Listed as contributor per
      emerging convention for AI-assisted software development; the AI
      system holds no copyright.
url: "https://github.com/awickert/r.richdem"
license: GPL-3.0
keywords:
  - GRASS GIS
  - RichDEM
  - terrain analysis
  - hydrology
  - depression hierarchy
  - fill-spill-merge
  - flow accumulation
  - digital elevation model
